Sulfotransferase rule attribution
=================================

The human N- and O-glycan sulfotransferase rules distributed with glyenzy were
selected and translated from GlycoEnzOnto:

https://github.com/neel-lab/GlycoEnzOnto

GlycoEnzOnto is described in:

Huang et al. (2022), "GlycoEnzOnto: a glycan-domain ontology for modeling
knowledge of glycan biosynthesis", Bioinformatics.
https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btac704

The source material is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International license (CC BY 4.0):

https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

For glyenzy, the source reactions were selected to retain canonical human
N- and O-glycan contexts, translated into glyenzy's IUPAC-condensed enzyme-rule
format, expanded from compact alternatives into explicit rules, and supplied
with explicit context requirements where needed. Reactions limited to
glycosaminoglycans or O-Xyl glycans, glycolipids, protein sulfation, sulfate
removal, donor synthesis, or transport were excluded.
